		"desc" : "Phonetics is the systematic study of the human ability to make and hear sounds which use the vocal organs of speech, especially for producing oral language.\n
The three branches of Phonetics are\n
-	Articulatory Phonetics:Production of human speech sound.\n
-	Auditory Phonetics:Reception of sound by air.\n
-	Acoustic Phonetics:Physical characteristics of transmission of sound.\n
One of the most important tools of phonetics and phonology is a special alphabet called the International Phonetic Alphabet or IPA, a standardized representation of the sounds used in human language.  Reading and writing IPA will help you understand what's really happening when people speak.
