Phoneme: Minimal meaningful unit of distinctive sound features. For e.g. Phoneme /p/in /pat/ and /b/in /bat/.
Phone: Smallest possible segment of sound.\n
Allophone: Variation of phoneme. For e.g. /p/-[ 
Complementary distribution: If two allophones are not in contrast, is known as Complementary distribution.
Neutralization: Lack of contrast between two phonemes in a particular environment.\n
Free variation:Non significant linguistic variation between two or more linguistics form is known as free variation. For e.g. /ai/ and /i:/ in pronunciation of word “Either” etc",
